# Stepanovka, Mikhaylovsky Selsoviet, Bizhbulyaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Stepanovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Mikhaylovsky Selsoviet, Bizhbulyaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 6 as of 2010.
Geography
It is located 55&nbsp;km from Bizhbulyak and 15&nbsp;km from Mikhaylovka.
